      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "@MarcoFalke Ah, sorry: the reason for the potential deadlock warning (lock-order-inversion) is simply that the lock order between `cs_main` and `foo->cs_sendProcessing` differed between tests prior to this commit.\r\n\r\nAfter this commit the following lock order is used:\r\n\r\n```\r\n1. LOCK(cs_main);\r\n2. LOCK(foo->cs_sendProcessing);\r\n```\r\n\r\nPrior to this commit the following lock order was also used:\r\n\r\n```\r\n1. LOCK(foo->cs_sendProcessing);\r\n2. LOCK(cs_main);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is part of the `-fsanitize=thread` output:\r\n\r\n```\r\nWARNING: ThreadSanitizer: lock-order-inversion (potential deadlock) (pid=20357)\r\n  Cycle in lock order graph: M6554537 (0x55cf759864f8) => M453033967624932984 (0x000000000000) => M6554537\r\n\r\n  Mutex M453033967624932984 acquired here while holding mutex M6554537 in main thread:\r\n  Ã¢ÂÂ¦\r\n    #8 DoS_tests::outbound_slow_chain_eviction::test_method() /Ã¢ÂÂ¦/bitcoin/src/test/DoS_tests.cpp:74:5 (test_bitcoin+0x376064)\r\n    #9 DoS_tests::outbound_slow_chain_eviction_invoker() /Ã¢ÂÂ¦/bitcoin/src/test/DoS_tests.cpp:55:1 (test_bitcoin+0x375782)\r\n  Ã¢ÂÂ¦\r\n  Mutex M6554537 acquired here while holding mutex M453033967624932984 in main thread:\r\n  Ã¢ÂÂ¦\r\n    #8 PeerLogicValidation::InitializeNode(CNode*) /Ã¢ÂÂ¦/bitcoin/src/net_processing.cpp:581:9 (test_bitcoin+0x8b955c)\r\n    #9 DoS_tests::DoS_banning::test_method() /Ã¢ÂÂ¦/bitcoin/src/test/DoS_tests.cpp:201:16 (test_bitcoin+0x379a18)\r\n    #10 DoS_tests::DoS_banning_invoker() /Ã¢ÂÂ¦/bitcoin/src/test/DoS_tests.cpp:178:1 (test_bitcoin+0x378e42)\r\n```",
